headline: Millennials Show Increased Interest in Buying a Home Despite High Mortgage Rates, Realtor.com速 Survey Finds
summary: Millennials are the only generation with a greater interest in buying a home in the next six months compared to September 2024 according to a new survey from Realtor.com速. Millennials' buying intention grew to 23% this year compared to last September (15%), although most Americans (69%) are not planning to engage in a real estate transaction in the next six months.
